HEADWORD: Upburst
<hw>Up"burst`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of bursting
upwards; a breaking through to the surface; an upbreak or uprush;
<as>as, an <ex>upburst</ex> of molten matter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

